  "properties": {
    "long_instructions": "# Campaign Pitch Examples\r\n\r\n#### The final deliverable of the Internet Access Advocacy Campaign Project is a campaign pitch. Read each of the example pitches below.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #F5F7F8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px;\">\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \"><strong>Example 1</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \">How many times have you scrolled through social media and felt like everyone else’s life was perfect? The truth is, social media is designed to keep us hooked—but research shows it’s also impacting our mental health in ways we don’t even realize.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \">That’s why our advocacy campaign is focused on raising awareness about the link between social media and teen mental health. Our audience is high school students like us, and we want them to take control of their screen time and push for social media companies to be more transparent about their impact on mental health.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #F5F7F8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px;\">\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \"><strong>Example 2</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \">The numbers don’t lie: A 2023 study found that teens who spend more than three hours a day on social media are twice as likely to experience anxiety and depression. Apps like Instagram and TikTok use endless scrolling and algorithm-driven content to keep us on longer—yet they rarely warn us about the negative effects.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #F5F7F8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px;\">\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \"><strong>Example 3</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \">So, what’s the solution? First, we’re launching a social media campaign with infographics and videos that break down how these platforms affect our brains. Second, we’re writing a letter to lawmakers urging them to require social media companies to give users more control over their feeds and screen time tracking tools.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \">We all love social media—but we should be the ones in control, not the algorithm. It’s time to make social media healthier for everyone!\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n## 📝 To Do\r\n\r\n#### Choose one Example Pitch to provide feedback on. In the reflection box below, answer the following questions based on your example.\r\n* #### Does the campaign clearly address the digital divide and/or net neutrality?\r\n* #### Are the proposed solutions realistic?\r\n* #### What is one strength of this campaign?\r\n* #### What is one area that could be improved?\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: left; margin:20px 0px 30px 0px\">\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/teaching-the-fabric-of-the-internet-and-ai-pl-reflection-example-pitch-feedback/41005\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/7dbe63a051fbad4ef262d6ab710e2966-image-1731959037460.png\" style=\"width: auto; height: 100px;\"  alt=\"A browser with two text boxes, both including an avatar and lines of text.\"></a>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #007786; border-radius: 20px 20px 20px 20px; color: #000000; width: 80%; margin-left: 5%; margin-right: 5%; padding: 10px 10px 5px 10px;\">\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Post to the Code.org Forum</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.2; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\">Share your response and read other educators' ideas on the forum! Click on the icon to the left to direct to our forum post.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n#### While you’re reviewing in the forum think about: *What makes good and effective feedback? What type of feedback will I aim to provide to students? What type of feedback do I want students to provide to each other?*\r\n",
